00473,NULL,'right','Helen doesn\'t look like this any more','yes','no',NULL,3,0,'cf_public/artistDetailsP.cfm?actID=37','yes',0),(37,'2014-01-05 00:17:26','\"Keep Breathing\" by The Durutti Column','Working one-on-one with Manchester\'s favourite guitarist and composer of beautiful guitar music, Vini Reilly, I supplied the programming, arrangements, sound engineering, production and some instrumental accompaniment, for this entire album that was subsequently released on Artful Records to critical acclaim. ',00000463,NULL,'right','Album cover photo by Rachel McFarlane','yes','no',NULL,3,7,'cf_public/recsearchP.cfm?searchstring=keep%20breathing&editPage=7','yes',1),(38,'2014-01-05 00:17:28','Sounds of South America','From time to time when I come across an interesting noise or sound I get out my portable sound recorder and make a recording',00001088,NULL,'right','Travel Recorder','yes','no',NULL,3,6,'cf_public/recSearchP.cfm?searchstring=ambience&rowpref=14&currentpage=1&CFID=1400&CFTOKEN=87673187','yes',1),(39,'2014-01-05 00:09:25','The last Music I made','<p>I was in a hostel in El Bolson, Patagonia and found a nice guitar that inspired me to write this tune which I named &quot;<a href=\"../cfm/recDetailsP.cfm?recID=510\">El Pueblito</a>&quot;, the name of the hostel.</p>',00001637,NULL,'right','no image caption','yes','no',7,2,0,'cf_public/recDetailsP.cfm?currentpage=1&searchstring=el%20bolson','yes',0),(40,'2014-01-05 00:17:29','Tagangero Rapper fights back','Colombia, where political corruption and gang rule are ever-present, has spawned a new breed of young musician who\'s mission is to fight back against the injustice that their society has to live with on a day to day basis.\r\n<p>In Taganga I met just such a young man, Felipe-Luis Sanchez, who wanted to get his voice heard. Together we recorded this track, \"Del La Bola Roja\" a song about the drug gangs that hold his small town in a vice-like grip - they can be seen hanging out at the pool hall named \"la Bola Roja\" or \"the red ball\"',00000489,NULL,'right','no image caption','yes','no',NULL,3,9,'http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy_nu_3/cf_public/recDetailsP.cfm?currentpage=1&searchstring=roja','yes',1),(43,'2014-01-05 00:17:30','Settling in to a new life in Prague','<p>Its been over nine months now since we arrived back from South America and we\'ve found our feet a bit. Petra\'s beautiful and spacious apartment on the border of Vinohrady and Zizkov was available after the old tenant moved out and so we took it as our new home. <br />\r\nWe both have been working hard to establish ourselves here - Petra as an Investor Relations Consultant and me as a Web Developer. I\'m building a web content management system for companies that need to manage their Investor Relations areas within their corporate websites. Its a big project and not very music-related, but that\'s not necessarily a bad thing.....<br />\r\nSo not much music being made at the moment, just the occasional strum on the old guitar. I\'m taking classes in Czech twice a week and so far it\'s going well. Yesterday I earned two sweets for being top of the class! Fanstastick&yacute;! Some of those words are quite tricky to pronounce though - having a musical ear is quite a help here...they forgot to put the vowels in most of the words and so learning to say them is best done by listening carefully to how they say them</p>',00001662,NULL,'left','no image caption','yes','no',1,4,4,'','yes',1),(44,'2014-01-05 00:17:31','What to do if the player keeps playing the same track','<p>Unfortunately this site experiences problems when you use Internet Explorer version 6 &amp; 7 (and Opera) to listen to the tracks.</p>\r\n<p>If you keep hearing the first recording that you listened to even when selecting a new one then it means that the browser is using a cached version of the player rather than downloading an updated one for each new track. \\more</p>\r\n<p>The simple answer is to view the site in Firefox and this problem should not occur.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if you only have Internet Explorer available then you may delete the browser\'s cache before attempting to listen to a new recording. Follow these steps:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Go to the Tools menu and select &quot;Delete Browsing History&quot;</li>\r\n    <li>Click on the &quot;Delete Files&quot; button.</li>\r\n    <li>Click &quot;yes&quot;</li>\r\n    <li>Close the dialogue box</li>\r\n    <li>Press the F5 key to reload the page and you should then be able to listen to the next recording.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the same reasons Opera (the browser, not the type of music) is not recommended either, at least until the problem has been solved. That should happen very soon during the next update of the web site.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your patience</p>',00001660,NULL,'right','no image caption','no','no',2,4,5,'','yes',1),(45,'2014-01-05 00:32:43','Petra\'s Portfolio Web Site Now Ready!','<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">After <i>literally</i> <em>months</em> of work selecting and programming we have finally finished Petra\'s Photographic Portfolio. I have even built a special content management system so that she can update it herself. Its called Fotocheck and its one of the main projects that I\'ve been working on recently since living here in Prague. So..... if you want to see Petra\'s fantastic pictures then click this </span><a href=\"http://www.petraroberts.cz\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">www.petraroberts.cz</span></span></a></p>',00000284,NULL,'left','One of Petra\'s Photos','yes','no',2,3,3,'http://www.petralapkova.com','yes',1),(47,'2009-05-18 15:34:54','this should be at the top','<p>gffdgdfgfdsgdfgd</p>',00001667,NULL,'right','','no','yes',1,3,0,NULL,'yes',0),(49,'2008-04-04 05:38:49','This also should be at the top','<p>sdfsdfsdsd</p>',00001663,NULL,'right','','no','no',6,4,0,NULL,'yes',0),(60,'2008-03-26 13:00:00','Xoundboy (Ben Roberts)','<p>Xoundboy.com is a portoflio of sound recordings made by myself, Ben Roberts, a freelance sound engineer / musician / producer originally from Nottingham, UK.</p>\r\n<p>Until June 2006 I was based in Manchester. I then spent a year touring around South America with my wife Petra on the look-out for original artists to record and promote. Since June 2007 I have been living in Prague setting up as a web developer and building this web site, amongst others. I hope to return to doing music one day soon and plan to build a new recording studio in the near future.</p>\r\n<p>This website contains the best work I have been involved with.</p>\r\n<p>The design and programming of the site is all my own work, originally based upon the old transistor radio that my Mum gave to me when I was about seven years old. That one was permanently tuned into BBC Radio 2 ... the tuning knob had stopped working. I took the radio to pieces in a desperate attempt to make it receive other stations but unfortunately when I put it all back together again it had completely stopped working. I was distraught. Thirty years later I have banished that painful memory forever (hopefully) by creating this fully-working virtual model that is permanently tuned to &quot;Radio Xoundboy&quot;...</p>',00001671,NULL,'right','Petra and I on tour in Patagonia last year','yes','no',11,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(56,'2008-03-27 13:00:00','Planning a trip to Saturn','',00001670,NULL,'right','Saturn','yes','no',4,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(57,'2008-03-25 13:14:59','no, THIS should be at the top really','',00000001,NULL,'right','','no','yes',0,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(61,'2014-01-05 19:24:40','The 80\'s','<p>In 1983, when we were thirteen years old there were a few of us at school that wanted to be rock stars. We listened to Iron Maiden, Kiss, Rainbow and Dio, grew our hair to be as long as our mothers would let us (which wasn\'t very long really) and bought as many heavy metal records as we could afford (quite a few, because we were too young to buy anything else more exciting) and wore denim jackets (because our mothers wouldn\'t let us wear leather biker jackets).\\more</p>\r\n<p>My mate James\' Dad was quite cool and used to take us to see the bands when they came to Nottigham\'s Royal Concert Hall. At school one morning, during break when we were smoking cigarettes on &quot;the Forest&quot; we decided to form a heavy rock band - luckily we all had different instrumental aspirations - Adam wanted to play drums, James (who\'s mum had just bought him a blue leather motorcycle jacket... with tassles!) wanted to play bass and I wanted to play electric guitar. Even luckier, our parents were all very supportive (little did they know what they had in store!) and helped us to get our instruments. Our first band\'s name?....&quot;Overture&quot;, like the opening of an opera.. (thanks for the name, Mum).</p>\r\n<p>We practised hard for a year and got a set together. Our first gig, a 4-band line-up, that we organised ourselves in the &quot;Founder Hall&quot; at school, was named &quot;Doctor Rock&quot; because we decided to give all of the proceeds to our favourite charity - Dr. Barnado\'s (actually we were told to by the headmaster). We would have programmed ourselves as the headline act but for the fact that two years above us existed a band of legendary prowess and quality. Their name? .....&quot;Beeston Carpark&quot;, named after one of their favourite car parks in Beeston, a suburb of Nottingham. We took to the stage in special outfits that I had made on my mum\'s sewing machine the night before. The show was a huge success and still lives on in our memories as a 24 karat diamond-of-a-memory in the rough of all those subsequent gigs where we could never quite achieve the same heady heights of rock stardom that we did on that first outing. The obvious next step was to record our demo tape...</p>\r\n<div class=\"news_image\">Seven songs recorded and mixed in two days, I was filled with wonder and amazement and silly questions like &quot;the guitar sounds out of time...can you make it sound in time?&quot; because I wasn\'t good enough to play it properly. &quot;...no, its impossible&quot;. This was in the days before digital. Here\'s a taste of that first recording session: <a href=\"recording.php?recID=280\">High Society</a></div>\r\n<p>Old school friends still talk about those days fondly and in October \'06 there will be a special event to mark the 20th anniversary of the &quot;Cosmic Cavern&quot; a.k.a Dan\'s garage, another of our early venues where Overture shared a stage with another 80s uber-group-that-never-quite-made-it, &quot;The Kaftans&quot;, fronted by Dan himself.</p>\r\n<p>All good things come to an end, as do good relations between band-members and Overture split with James and Adam going off to pursue other musical avenues, leaving me to find my way on my own. It was a dark and barren time for all of us (but probably quite a good thing in retrospect, because we had to take our O levels anyway!).</p>\r\n<p>While acid house music was big in the late 80s me and my friends were rebelling against electronic music and playing in a new band at school. In our band we hated all electronic music because it sounded artificial and we didn\'t understand it. (Actually I secretly really liked &quot;Charlie&quot; by the Prodigy, but was too scared to say!). Moreover, at the time this strange and bleepily-contrived noise was threatening to squeeze proper music like ours, made by guitars, off the musical map, so we decided to wear Raybans and call our band &quot;Drum Machines Don\'t Wear Shades&quot; desperately clinging to the notion that we could beat these shaven-headed ravers with impeccable style and dress sense. At that point we hadn\'t yet seen how drum machines could be made to look highly appealing and stylish if you wore a couple of torches strapped to your bonce</p>',00001672,NULL,'left','design: Adam Firmin','yes','no',11,2,0,NULL,'yes',0),(62,'2014-01-05 19:25:34','The 90\'s','<p>We left school, our band split up and Leeds University beckoned after a year off galivanting around South-East Asia and Australia. Continuing on the theme of dodgy names I joined a Bradford-based band called &quot;The Barbarelles&quot; (- we were hoping that Jane Fonda might actually turn up to one of our gigs dressed up as Barbarella, but she never did! Ah Well!) We recorded a few songs at Martin Cooper\'s (the guitarist from Beeston Carpark who left school early to start a small recording studio).Here is one of the songs, <a href=\"recording.php?recID=340\">Mr B</a>, still sounding fresh nearly 20 years on. \\more</p>\r\n<p>It was around about that time that I first heard the miraculous album &quot;Blue Lines&quot; by Massive Attack and one day Jim, our keyboard player, lent me his Korg M1 synth along with his Atari ST. That really inspired me and opened my eyes and ears to the concept that sound could now really be manipulated in the studio and that the only limit is your imagination. I realised that there was absolutely nothing to fear about electronics in music because the end product is the important thing - not the means of production. By now I was also listening to a real mixture of artists like the Red Hot Chili Peppers, The Orb, Gil Scott Heron, Van Morrison, Aretha Franklin, Public Enemy and of course, Jimi Hendrix and The Doors as well as some classical and jazz. The Positiva Ambient Collection CD lived permanently in my CD player for about a year.</p>\r\n<p>I left university, our band split up and France beckoned. I took a TEFL course and decided that I needed to learn a foreign language and French was the easy option - plus Julia, my girlfriend at the time, really wanted to live there. Just as we were about to leave she got offered a place at drama school in London so I went on my own. I managed to buy a few bits of gear, packed my car full of stuff and drove south. My first studio consisted of an old Amiga computer, a small midi keyboard and a miniature tone generator called a Yamaha TG100. It didn\'t have much scope for editting sounds (although I learnt to program its system exclusive messages in a desperate attempt to gain more control of its sounds) Here is the first track I made (in my tiny bedsit flat in Toulouse, France) Mermaid It took more than three weeks to make (a bit like this website).</p>\r\n<p>Due to lack of money and no work available as an english teacher (not that I looked terribly hard) Bradford beckoned again as I had been offered a place in Jon Gibbons\' new band. We decided to call our band &quot;Egomania&quot; due to the fact that there was an abundance of self-regard that verged on the unhealthy. We made an album &quot;Paris or New Orleans&quot; signed to a management company in London and never got anywhere other than on each other\'s nerves. A familiar story, or so I\'m told. Here is Out of the Blue, also recorded at Martin Cooper\'s.</p>\r\n<p>By 1993 I was fed up of being in good bands that never got anywhere. A group of DJs with funny accents (from Warminster, near Bath) were living round the corner and operating under the name PSI Division. Another slightly older DJ called Pogo was also on the scene and he was from a crew called The Spawnee Posse who had been famously organising free parties for people who liked to do that sort of thing. He took me into their cellar and showed me a collection of old PA gear and said &quot;we need a sound engineer with a van&quot;. I still had the big Mercedes 508D splitter van I\'d bought for Egomania which was currently serving as a ridiculously huge run-around, plus, I knew how to plug speakers into amps and so at that moment I declared myself a sound engineer just so that I could get my hands on this very large and heavy sound-system that none of them could afford to maintain or move. And so despite my earlier scorn of electronic music I found myself involved with one of the most serious acid house party organisations in the north of England. It just seemed like a good idea at the time.</p>\r\n<p>This crazy music that never stopped until either the generator ran out of petrol or the police turned up and told everyone to move on had got under my skin and I turned my entire attention towards making some of it. I borrowed a load of money, bought some good equipment and set to work with funny-talking DJ mate Liam to make house music. We hadn\'t got a clue but enjoyed the process thoroughly. We went over to Manchester one day in the van to see Liam\'s mate Stefan, another DJ and musician but who was actually quite good. Going under the name &quot;A Positive Life&quot; he\'d had a successful hit tune and seemed to know everything about electronic music production. I was especially in awe of his new album that had come out on Beyond Records. It seemd that I\'d met someone who was doing what I dreamed of doing and was making money from selling his music, this gave me hope and inspiration. I pressed on and made some tunes that were actually getting a good response. Here\'s one called ReKat.</p>\r\n<p>By mid-1994 our Spawnee Posse activities had us running around doing gigs left-right and centre and we\'d decided that free parties were great but really we ought to try to make some money to pay our expenses. Bradford\'s nightclubs were small and notoriously difficult to fill with the type of people we were looking for whereas Manchester had a vibrant music scene and over ten thousand students. Our fortnightly gig at the Roadhouse was getting so popular that we moved to the larger Phoenix and ran a sequence of nights called &quot;Out of Order&quot;. It was only a matter of time before we packed everything in the van and moved lock stock and barrel to Chorlton, Manchester</p>\r\n<p>When we did really big parties and needed more speakers I used to go round to see a guy called Strat who had some. One day he took me to his lock up and said &quot;I need a sound engineer with a van&quot;</p>\r\n<!-- InstanceEndEditable -->',00001697,NULL,'right','','yes','no',11,3,0,NULL,'yes',0),(63,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','Gorse Hill Studios','<p align=\"left\">In early 2000, after being commissioned by Trafford M.B.C. Youth Service to design and install a recording studio in a Youth Centre in Manchester, I then took the role of project manager, building the studio into a nationally recognised youth music project. \\more</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">At first I ran music production workshops and &quot;taster sessions&quot; with groups of young people from the various youth centres around the borough. This quickly evolved into the &quot;Ten Hour Project&quot; whereby an artist or group receives 10 hours of free studio time with a professional music producer.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">These sessions, along with the &quot;Gorse Hill Studios Vol 1 &amp; 2&quot; promo CDs and the &quot;Side Show 1 &amp; 2&quot; live performance showcase events were to be the launchpad for several successful careers in the music industry.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Working in multiple roles (studio manager, fund-raiser, workshop leader, sound engineer, producer and maintenance engineer) I eventually decided after four years service that I had given all that I could to the project.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Today, run by Ottilia Ordog, Mandy Wigby and Richard Sliwa, the staff team that I appointed during my time there as studio manager, Gorse Hill Studios is still going strong and continues to be one of the central pillars that support Manchester\'s vibrant youth music movement.</p>',00000482,NULL,'right','The vocal booth in Studio 1, Gorse Hill Studios','yes','no',3,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(64,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','\"Keep Breathing\" by the durutti column','<p>Working one-on-one with Manchester\'s favourite guitarist and composer of beautiful guitar music, Vini Reilly, I supplied the programming, arrangements, sound engineering, production and some instrumental accompaniment, for this entire album that was subsequently released on Artful Records to critical acclaim.</p>',00000463,NULL,'right','Album Photo: Rachel McFarlane','yes','no',3,3,0,NULL,'yes',0),(65,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','Walk the Plank Fireshow Soundtracks','<p align=\"left\">Since the mid 1990s I have regularly been commissioned to work on soundtracks to large-scale fireshows produced by Walk the Plank Pyrotechnics, a cutting edge fireworks company based in Salford, UK. \\more</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">These commissions include, amongst others, programming and composition for the soundtrack to the world-renowned production of &quot;The Tower of Light&quot;, a pyrotechnic animation of a lighthouse where performing lighthouse keepers run all over its 40-foot steel structure as it comes to life in a spectacular blaze of fire, sparks and explosions.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">More recently, working alongside Barnsley-based poet Ian McMillan, I was commissioned to compose the music for &quot;Remember, Remember&quot; a fireshow that took place on 5th November 2005 in London to commemorate the 400th aniversary of Guy Fawkes\' gunpowder plot. In this version of events he was successful! 20,000 people watched as a 100-foot high wooden replica of the Houses of Parliament went up in flames.</p>',00000950,NULL,'left','','yes','no',3,2,0,NULL,'yes',0),(66,'2008-04-04 06:20:42','This Website! (http://www.xoundboy.com)','<p>After nearly fifteen years of working on hundreds of diverse projects I realised that the best examples of this work lacked an effective means of presentation. A website seemed to be the only way forward.</p>\r\n<p>Unable to stand the thought of letting someone else be in control of this website I decided to learn about HTML and how to use Dreamweaver, Fireworks and Flash. Then I had the bright idea of adding an online database so then I had to learn Coldfusion, SQL, UNIX and MySQL administration as well as how to configure Coldfusion, PHP, Apache and MySQL testing servers plus a lot more.</p>\r\n<p>Not recommended for the faint of heart!</p>',00000946,NULL,'right','My original design for the homepage (you are currently looking at version 3, if not later)','no','yes',3,2,0,NULL,'yes',0),(68,'2009-02-08 04:57:28','Program of Events for the Wedding Day','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Here you will find a provisional schedule for the Wedding Day. Some timings may be subject to change and there will almost certainly be more added to this over the coming weeks as our organisational machine gets up to speed: \\more<br />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"> </span></span></p>\r\n<table cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"2\" border=\"1\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" style=\"width: 570px; height: 278px;\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">09:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Breakfast at your Hotel</b></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">We advise everyone to eat a proper breakfast as the reception will not start until 2pm. If you miss breakfast then there\'s a Starbuck\'s not far from the wedding ceremony venue in Malostranske Namesti.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">10:30</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Transport</b></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Family members will be picked up at the hotel by cars. We will hopefully be able to organise some minibuses for those of you who aren\'t staying in the immediate vicinity of the wedding <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/cfm/details.cfm?contentID=72\">(see the transport page)</a></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">11:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Arrival at the Ceremony Venue</b></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">We ask that all guests arrive at the gate to Vrtbovska Zahrada by 11am where the UshBridesmaids will be waiting to greet you.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">11:30</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Marriage Ceremony</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">This should take place on the upper terrace of Vrtbovska Zahrada unless it\'s raining in which case it will happen in the Sala Terra on the bottom level.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">12:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Congratulations</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Form an orderly queue please!</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">12:15</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Group Photography</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">The obligatory group-photos.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">12:30</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Bride &amp; Groom photos</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">While we are having our photos taken you wedding guests are welcome to walk around the gardens and admire the beautiful surroundings and make remarks like &quot;ooh, aren\'t they a lovely couple!&quot;</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">12:45</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Wedding Party leaves and makes its way up the hill to the Reception Venue</strong></td>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <p style=\"text-align: left;\">The able-bodied will then walk, led by the Bridesmaids and Ushers, in a long caterpillar-type procession up through a beautiful hillside orchard which by 3<sup>rd</sup> May should be in full bloom (no special climbing equipment required). Petrin Hill, otherwise known as &quot;the Lovers\' Hill&quot;, plays host to our wedding reception venue that offers a stunningly beautiful view over Prague. For those people who don\'t fancy the climb there\'s a fenicular railway that is a mere ten minutes walk along a flat footpath from Vrtbovska Zahrada. Take the train up to the first stop and the reception is a two minute walk on the right hand side back towards the Castle.</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">13:15</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Welcome Drink</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">By the time you get up the hill you\'ll be good and ready for a nice glass of one of the Czech Republic\'s finest beverages.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">14:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Lunch</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Seated lunch for all invited guests on the Terrace. Vegetarian options are available but please let us know in advance. Smokers will be pleased to know that it is still legal to smoke here.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">15:30</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Speeches</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">AAaaaaaarrrrggghhhhhh!!!!&nbsp; The cause of many a sleepless night for the speakers I\'m sure. Please be polite and laugh heartily.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">16:30</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Wedding Cake &amp; Coffee</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">....and a stroll around the Orchard if it\'s a nice day.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">17:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Activities</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Traditional English and Czech Wedding-type activities. Actually if anyone has any ideas about possible activites please feel free to add a comment below.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">18:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>DJs</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Music....and possibly some dancing from the early-starters.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">18:30</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Evening Guests Arrive</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">An influx of fresh blood. Bear in mind that these people will not have been drinking so please don\'t frighten them too much!</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">19:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Barbecue</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">This will be done in the traditional Czech style and something to look forward to, especailly for the non-veggies (veggie options also available).</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">21:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">The Superstar Wedding DJ Competition</span></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Don\'t hold back... if you think you can....or even if you don\'t.....pack a memory stick with some killer dancefloor tunes and stake your claim to the title of &quot;Superstar Wedding DJ&quot;</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">23:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>DJs</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Dancing. Strat, Mully and myself will be donning our DJ hats, breaking out the rope lights and (hopefully) getting everyone up on their feet for a right good boogie. Playlist suggestions welcome.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">12:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>End of the Free Bar</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">Did we mention that we\'ll be buying the wine, beer and soft drinks?</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">1:00</td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Petrinske Terasy Closes...</strong></td>\r\n            <td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n            <p>....supposedly, although the landlord did tell us that if it\'s a good party he\'ll let us stay later.</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">After that we\'ll be off to our posh hotel for our first night of wedded bliss, so you\'ll be on your own then. There are supposed to be lots of nightclubs in Prague though and if anyone really wants to keep partying then we suggest you go clubbing.</p>',00001689,NULL,'right','Vrtbovska Zahrada with Prague Castle and St Nicholas Church in the Background','yes','no',5,9,0,NULL,'yes',0),(69,'2009-02-08 04:57:38','Useful Maps','<p>I\'ve done my own Google-Earth style Zoom-in from outer space! Not quite as technologically advanced but all you really need, nevertheless.. \\more</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>....just scroll down</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>(if the comments box appears in front of the maps then just press F5 to refresh the page once all of the maps have downloaded)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- the earth -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>The Earth</p>\r\n<img src=\"../images/user/earth.png\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<!-- europe -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>Europe (The Czech Republic is at the centre)</p>\r\n<img src=\"../images/user/europe.png\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<!--  C.R. -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>The Czech Republic</p>\r\n<img src=\"../images/user/CzechRepublicMap.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<!-- Greater Prague --->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>Prague and suburbs</p>\r\n<img alt=\"Greater Prague\" src=\"../images/user/Greater_Prague.png\" /></div>\r\n<!-- Prague centre -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>Prague City Map (click map to get a zoomable version)</p>\r\n<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\"><img width=\"800\" onclick=\"MM_openBrWindow(\'../images/user/city-detail.gif\',\'map\',\'toolbar=yes,location=yes,status=yes,scrollbars=yes,resizable=yes\')\" alt=\"Centre\" src=\"../images/user/city-detail_800.gif\" /></a></div>\r\n<!-- the wedding route -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>The Route for the wedding day</p>\r\n<img alt=\"route\" src=\"../images/user/route_map_800.png\" /></div>\r\n<!-- metro -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>The Metro System</p>\r\n<img alt=\"metro\" src=\"../images/user/metro.gif\" /></div>\r\n<!-- tram lines -->\r\n<div class=\"contentItem_centre\">\r\n<p>The Metro/Tram System (click map to get a zoomable version)</p>\r\n<a href=\"javascript:void(0);\"><img onclick=\"MM_openBrWindow(\'../images/user/prague-metro-trams-plan.gif\',\'\',\'toolbar=yes,location=yes,status=yes,menubar=yes,scrollbars=yes,resizable=yes\')\" alt=\"metro and tram\" src=\"../images/user/prague-metro-trams-plan_800.gif\" /></a></div>',00001686,NULL,'left','','yes','no',5,11,0,NULL,'yes',0),(70,'2009-02-08 04:57:54','Accommodation','<p>We really hope that you have your accommodation sorted out already but we suspect that there may still be a few people who haven\'t. If you\'re one of them then there\'s still a chance you can get something fairly decent, however a lot of places are fully booked already and you may have to spend a little time on Google.</p>\r\n<p>Click <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/downloadable_files/accom_list.pdf\">HERE</a> to download the accommodation list document that we sent out a couple of months ago.</p>\r\n<p>If you get stuck then please get in touch. Our phone numbers are:</p>\r\n<p>Ben +420 775 713 373</p>\r\n<p>Petra +420 603 489 663</p>',00001688,NULL,'right','This room is booked already!','yes','no',5,14,0,NULL,'yes',0),(71,'2014-01-05 00:17:36','Are you coming to Prague for the Wedding?','<p>If we\'ve invited you to our wedding then you can get lots of information here on Xoundboy.com about everything from Accommodation to Zoo opening hours! and of course interesting stuff like the &quot;Program of Events&quot;. Use the login details we sent to your email address to login <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/cfm/login.cfm\">HERE</a></p>',00001682,NULL,'right','','no','no',2,2,2,NULL,'yes',1),(72,'2009-02-08 04:57:32','Transport on the Wedding Day -- UPDATED MON 28TH APRIL --','<p><b>Family</b></p>\r\n<p>All family members will be picked up from their respective hotels between 10:45 and 11:15.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Friends</b></p>\r\n<p>We originally planned to pick everyone up in a bus but it turned out to be too much of a logistical problem to solve so we have abandoned this plan. Please make sure that you book your taxis well in advance to arrive on time. See <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/cfm/details.cfm?contentID=98\">THIS</a> article about how to get to the ceremony on time.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001684,NULL,'left','An old-fashioned tram','yes','no',5,10,0,NULL,'yes',0),(73,'2009-02-08 04:57:23','CONFIRMATION OF ACCEPTANCE','<p>With there being quite a lot of you, the task of keeping track of who\'s actually coming and who isn\'t, along with details of when you\'re arriving and leaving, where you\'re staying etc. has got a little out of hand. So we would be most grateful if all of you could take the time to..</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"color: Red;\"><a href=\"../cfm_secure/accommodation_form.cfm\">SEND CONFIRMATION</a></h3>\r\n<p>...as soon as possible</p>\r\n<p>Thanks</p>',00001685,NULL,'right','One of the first EMA - PRG Easyjet flights. Oh how they\'ve improved (not!) ','yes','no',5,8,0,NULL,'no',0),(74,'2008-05-06 13:00:00','Wedding Presents','<p>The Wedding List will remain open until around the 21st June.</p>\r\n<p>Arranging to buy an item is very easy. Just click <a href=\"https://www.johnlewisgiftlist.com/giftint/JSPs/GiftList/BuyGifts/GuestFindAList.jsp\">HERE</a> and enter the following gift list number: \\more</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">313833</span></b></p>\r\n<p>The rest is quite self-explanatory but here are a few things that you might need to know...</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>once you select and purchase an item then it will automatically be removed from the list so that no-one else can buy the same thing</li>\r\n    <li>we have arranged for John Lewis to deliver any un-collected gifts to my Mum\'s and we\'ll be driving over this summer so we can pick these up then</li>\r\n    <li>If you wish to, you can go into a branch of John Lewis and ask to purchase a gift from the list so that you may bring it over to Prague when you come for the wedding</li>\r\n    <li>for more information click <a href=\"https://www.johnlewisgiftlist.com/giftint/JSPs/GiftList/CustomerServices/CustomerService3.jsp\">HERE</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001687,NULL,'left','Don\'t get us one of these please','yes','no',5,15,0,NULL,'yes',0),(75,'2009-02-08 04:57:48','The Morning After the Night Before ... change of plan!','<p>&nbsp;Originally we were going to suggest going for Sunday Brunch but we just found out that our hotel does \'Breakfast in Bed\'.....</p>\r\n<p>...instead&nbsp; we\'re now planning a meal at our favourite Brazilian restaurant (Brasilero) just off the old-town square.</p>\r\n<p>According to Damian, Clive has booked somewhere for breakfast </p>',00001690,NULL,'right','','yes','no',5,13,0,NULL,'yes',0),(94,'2009-02-08 04:57:19','Ben\'s last (planned) night of Bachelorhood (friday 2 May)','<p>It\'s probably not a wise idea to go out the night before you get married especially if you\'re the groom. Actually&nbsp; it\'s hard to imagine that a bride would be so foolish. The mind boggles at the infinite number of bad things that could happen to the poor boy on the eve of his nuptials. Ideally the altar-bound groom would be in bed by 9pm curled up with a mug of cocoa and pondering his future life of wedded bliss before getting a good night\'s sleep so that when he wakes up on the wedding morning he\'s fresh and full of life, ready to co-star in the biggest day of his life. \\more</p>\r\n<p>Having said all that I am unable to resist this perfect opportunity to go out in Prague and celebrate the end of my bachelorhood first with a meal with my family and then with a group of my friends (who despite their jesting about getting me drunk, shaving off my eyebrows and dumping me naked on an express train to Bratislava) will make sure that I don\'t peak too early and deliver me safely to Sir Toby\'s Hostel where I hope they still have a bed for me to sleep the night.</p>\r\n<p>So if you\'re a member of my family then I\'ll see you at 7pm at U Zlate Studne, the restauarant of the Golden Well Hotel situated right below the castle by the terraced gardens. (please note this is not the same place as the Golden Wheel Hotel where a lot of the Roberts family will be staying.</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile Damian and Richard will be going to a pub called U Provaznice (the Rope Maker\'s Wife), near Wenceslas Square, where we have booked a table for 15-20 people. I\'ll be coming along to join them at around 9pm and hope to see as many of you as possible too. If you would like to come just add a comment below saying so.</p>\r\n<p>They serve excellent traditional Czech food and very nice beer too although obviously I\'ll only be drinking fruit juice and mineral water!</p>\r\n<p>Click <a href=\"http://www.mapy.cz/#x=133079564@y=135942759@z=15@mm=ZP@sa=s@st=s@ssq=provaznice@sss=1@ssp=133069856_135931984_133094432_135955712\">HERE </a>for directions</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001712,NULL,'left','mmmmmm lovely orange juice!','yes','no',5,7,0,NULL,'yes',0),(76,'2009-02-08 04:58:04','Suggestions please...','<p>If anyone has any comments or suggestions about anything that we\'ve not covered on one of the other pages then this is the place to put them. Just post a comment.</p>',00001691,NULL,'left','','yes','no',5,17,0,NULL,'yes',0),(77,'2009-02-08 04:57:43','What to Wear?   --UPDATED MON 28TH APRIL --','<h2>The Ceremony &amp; Reception</h2>\r\n<p>We would like you to wear your best and most stylish clothes please...ladies in pretty frocks and gents in a suit and tie.</p>\r\n<p>Please bear in mind that the ceremony will be taking place outdoors as will the reception (although there will be alternative indoor heated areas if the weather turns bad). \\more We reccommend the ladies to pack a cardigan or jacket&nbsp; to wear if it gets a bit chilly and bring a brolly just in case it rains.</p>\r\n<p><u>Hats</u></p>\r\n<p>Ladies might also want to know whether or not to wear a hat. Well, here in the Czech Republic it\'s apparently quite unusual for ladies to wear hats at weddings in this day and age...so unless you really feel the urge to wear one you might not want to bother.</p>\r\n<p><u>Shoes</u></p>\r\n<p>High heels are probably not appropriate. Prague has a lot of cobble stones.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>The Evening Do</h2>\r\n<p>If you are just invited to the Evening Party but not the seated lunch then we don\'t &nbsp;really mind if you want to wear more casual clothing, although we would ask you not to wear T-shirts or trainers / sneakers - bear in mind that the Bridal Party will probably still all be dressed in their formal clothes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001694,NULL,'right','','yes','no',5,12,0,NULL,'yes',0),(78,'2014-01-05 00:17:38','Some notes about songs and credits','<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p><span class=\"courier-normal\">If you happen to be one of the artists that I have worked with and you can\'t find the song we did together in the &quot;RECORDINGS&quot; menu then please let me know and I\'ll try to add it. You will probably have to send me an MP3 of the song so that I can upload it as I do not have access to some of the recordings I have made.</span></p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p><span class=\"courier-normal\">If you find tracks that we made together and I have not added you to the credits then I apologise, I may have overlooked some people and their contributions. Just send me an email and I\'ll credit you.</span></p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p><span class=\"courier-normal\">If you find any mistakes in the credits please let me know and I\'ll correct them. </span></p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p><span class=\"courier-normal\">If you are unhappy about being associated with a particular recording then let me know and I\'ll remove you from the credits for that particular recording.</span></p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p><span class=\"courier-normal\">If you consider that by making a particular recording available for streaming without your permission that I am infringing your copyright and you would like me to remove the recording then please contact me and I will be happy to remove it. I apologise if this is the case. I cannot possibly contact all of the original writers and contributors to these recordings in advance and am assuming that no-one will mind.</span></p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p align=\"center\">PLEASE NOTE THAT ALL OF THE SOUND RECORDINGS FEATURED ON WWW.XOUNDBOY.COM ARE ONLY AVAILABLE TO BE STREAMED THROUGH A FLASH PLAYER AS MP3S OF 128Kb/s QUALITY AND ARE NOT BEING MADE AVAILABLE TO BE DOWNLOADED AT THIS STAGE</p>',00001695,NULL,'right','','yes','no',7,1,8,NULL,'yes',1),(79,'2008-05-07 03:16:58','Spotted a programming bug?','<p>This site, along with its custom-made content management system, is still being developed. It\'s been tested a little and appears to be working quite well but there\'s still the possibility that it may contain bugs or that pages may not load or display properly.</p>\r\n<p>If you notice anything that looks like a bug in the site programming then please let me know so that it can be fixed. \\more</p>\r\n<p>You may report any bugs by logging into the bug tracker</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/bugtrack\"> Click here for bug tracker </a></p>\r\n<p><u>Login Details</u></p>\r\n<p>username: guest</p>\r\n<p>password: guest</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Assign the project to &quot;Xoundbase&quot;, type a name for the bug and copy and paste the entire URL of the page that does not work properly into the &quot;Bug Desc&quot; box and then write as clear a description as possible of what went wrong along with what (if anything) happened immediately prior to the error.</p>\r\n<p>IMPORTANT: PLEASE STATE WHICH BROWSER AND WHICH VERSION NUMBER YOU ARE USING</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001696,NULL,'right','','yes','no',5,18,0,NULL,'no',0),(80,'2008-04-03 06:00:00','Contact Details','<p><b>Ben Roberts</b></p>\r\n<p>Radho&scaron;tsk&aacute; 1770/21</p>\r\n<p>130 00 Praha 3</p>\r\n<p>Czech Republic</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>email: <a href=\"mailto:ben@xoundboy.com\">ben@xoundboy.com</a></p>\r\n<p>mobile: +420 775 713 373</p>\r\n<p>ICQ: 446140877</p>',00001698,NULL,'right','','yes','no',6,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(81,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','This Website','<p>After nearly fifteen years of working on hundreds of diverse projects I realised that the best examples of this work lacked an effective means of presentation. A website seemed to be the only way forward. \\more</p>\r\n<p>Unable to stand the thought of letting someone else be in control of this website I decided to learn about HTML and how to use Dreamweaver, Fireworks and Flash. Then I had the bright idea of adding an online database so then I had to learn Coldfusion, SQL, UNIX and MySQL administration as well as how to configure Coldfusion, PHP, Apache and MySQL testing servers plus a lot more.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Not recommended for the faint of heart!</p>',00001699,NULL,'left','The original site design','yes','no',3,4,0,NULL,'yes',0),(82,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','Gorse Hill Studios - Digital Arts Suite','<p align=\"left\">A music and video technology and digital arts production classroom next-door to Studio 1 containing seven networked workstations providing the perfect environment in which to teach students how to program their own musical backing tracks as well as record and mix vocals. \\more</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">I designed and built the entire classroom from the ground up to be as easy to use and flexible as possible. Each workstation has good sound hardware consisting of analogue mixer, two pairs of headphones, midi keyboard and each computer is equipped with an excellent sound card.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">There is a large video projection screen that allows the demonstration of multi-media software such as Cubase or Photoshop, as well as a comprehensive audio distribution network that allows all of the recording spaces to be linked to any of the workstations if necessary. Users are required to login to the ultra-highspeed network that automatically backs up everyone\'s work as well as providing fast internet access and web-serving.</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">&nbsp;Networked scanners and printers (including a large-format poster printer) allow production of high quality print while professional video editting software, two video cameras together with a shotgun microphone enable video footage to be recorded on location, brought back to the studio and editted into short films.</p>',00000939,NULL,'right','The Digital Arts Suite','yes','no',3,5,0,NULL,'yes',0),(83,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','GHS Showcase CD Vol 1','<p>The first promo showcase CD to be made at Gorse Hill Studios in 2002. The limited run of 500 copies gave the best artists an opportunity to get their music heard by a wider audience.</p>',00001700,NULL,'left','Design: Sophie Choupas','yes','no',3,6,0,NULL,'yes',0),(84,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','GHS Showcase CD Vol II','<p>The second promo showcase CD from Gorse Hill artists, reputed to have been a much sought-after release amongst music industry scouts was completed a year after volume 1 and a run of 2000 copies released a lot of these being distributed to the audience of &quot;The Side Show 2&quot; as they left the concert.</p>',00000462,NULL,'right','Design: Sophie Choupas','yes','no',3,7,0,NULL,'yes',0),(85,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','\"These 4 Walls\" by Mossey','<p>Working with Manchester-based singer/songwriter Tom Leyden I co-performed, arranged, engineered and produced this album that has yet to be released.</p>',00000960,NULL,'left','','yes','no',3,8,0,NULL,'yes',0),(86,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','The Side Shows I & II','<p>The first Side Show event was supposed to be a small showcase event for the kids who came down the studio. It was so popular that we nearly had to stop the show because about 250 turned up (we expected about 80). \\more</p>\r\n<p>It took place in the Zion Arts Centre, Manchester. My first attempt at music event promotion taught me more than a person should be expected to learn in just one night!</p>\r\n<p>A year later we repeated the event at the Contact Theatre, Manchester. This time I had some help and we filled the large theatre space fuller than ever in its history. It was a massive success and shortly afterwards Raw T, one of the bands from the studio signed a record deal with Tony Wilson\'s &quot;Factory 4&quot; record label.</p>',00001702,NULL,'right','','yes','no',3,9,0,NULL,'yes',0),(87,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','Live recordings of the Durutti Column','<p>First at The Bridgewater Hall, Manchester then at St George\'s Hall, Brighton. Finally at Oklahoma in Manchester. These multi-track recordings were made to be used in the soundtrack for a DVD movie of &quot;A year in the life of Vini Reilly&quot;, enigmatic virtuouso guitarist/front-man of legendary Factory Records band, The Durutti Column. The movie has yet to be editted.</p>',00000480,NULL,'left','','yes','no',3,10,0,NULL,'yes',0),(88,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','Studios 1 - 8','<p>In each of the eight houses or apartments that I have lived in since 1993 there has been a music studio of varying degrees of complexity built by my own fair hands.</p>',00001707,NULL,'right','','yes','no',3,11,0,NULL,'yes',0),(89,'2008-04-03 13:00:00','\"The Amazing Syd Selby (& Fanny)\" Soundtrack','<p>This critically acclaimed tragi-comedy theatre piece from Motionloco Theatre Co. about Syd Selby, an ageing music hall magician and his long suffering assistant/spouse, Fanny, written, directed and starring the ultra-talented actor Terence Mann, ran for two weeks at the Royal Exchange Theatre, Manchester over Christmas 2004. Working together, Terence and I created a rich and inventive sound design that together with a clever script and split-second timing took the audience on an amazing journey into the psyche of this tormented individual.</p>',00001704,NULL,'left','','yes','no',3,12,0,NULL,'yes',0),(90,'2008-04-04 06:20:05',' \"Me & The King\" Soundtrack','<p>Building on the success of their first production, &quot;Syd &amp; Fanny&quot;, Motionloco\'s second theatre show, entitled &quot;Me &amp; the King&quot; is a surreal foray into the dark under-belly of an Elvis impersonator\'s disturbed subconscious.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The stage action is entwined with an ever-present ambient and musical soundtrack that adds an at-times twisted and dark, at others, uplifting and ecstatic dimension to this highly original and critically acclaimed piece of psycho-theatre.</p>',00001701,NULL,'right','','yes','no',3,13,0,NULL,'yes',0),(91,'2009-02-08 04:57:59','Getting to and from Prague Centre from the Airport','<p>Prague city centre is about 10 miles from its airport so you really need to plan in advance how you get from the airport to your hotel / hostel / apartment or cardboard box under the Charles Bridge.\\more</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><u>Option 1 -&nbsp; City Shuttle (Expensive but minimum stress)</u></p>\r\n<p>The easiest option is to use one of the &quot;City Shuttle&quot; cars that wait immediately outside the doors of the arrivals hall. One of these will charge around &pound;24 to take you into the city centre.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><u>Option 2 - Taxi (Save some money)</u></p>\r\n<p>If you would like to save some money but would still like a door-to-door service you could either arrange for your hotel to pick you up or ring one of the following taxi numbers when you arrive. Either of these options will cost around &pound;16.</p>\r\n<p>City Taxis +420 257 257 257</p>\r\n<p>Profi Taxi +420 844 700 800</p>\r\n<p>(WARNING: click <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/cfm/details.cfm?contentID=92\">here</a>)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><u>Option 3 - Bus / Metro/Tram (Cheap and cheerful)</u></p>\r\n<p>As you emerge into the arrivals hall make your way over to the right of the exit doors to where there is a row of counters. Go to the Prague City Transport counter and buy a ticket for 26 crowns (82 pence). There are some cash machines on the other side of the doors if you need to withdraw money.</p>\r\n<p>The bus into Prague leaves from right outside the arrivals hall - cross the road and go to the right most bus stop. Take the number 119 all the way to the last stop (make sure you frank your ticket when you get on the bus otherwise it\'s not valid)</p>\r\n<p>When you get off you should be at Dejvicka (pronounced &quot;David\'s Ska&quot;) metro station. Your ticket is valid for 75mins from the time you franked it and can be used on any bus, tram or metro in Prague. Take the metro the rest of the way into Prague and find your hotel.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001708,NULL,'right','Prague has a very nice airport called Ruzyne','yes','no',5,16,0,NULL,'yes',0),(92,'2009-02-08 04:58:09','Using Taxis (caution required)','<p>If you need a taxi while you\'re here in Prague we recommend you call one of the following companies.</p>\r\n<p>City Taxis +420 257 257 257</p>\r\n<p>Profi Taxis +420 844 700 800 \\more</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately it\'s a well-documented fact that the taxi drivers of Prague are quite likely to attempt to rip you off. We recommend you take a look at this site (click <a href=\"http://www.praguetaxi.co.uk/\">HERE</a>) to learn about how to avoid being over-charged.</p>\r\n<p>Luckily Prague has excellent public transport so for most of your stay it\'s very unlikely that you\'ll be wanting a cab.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001710,NULL,'left','If you get picked up by this one expect to pay at least quadruple!','yes','no',5,19,0,NULL,'yes',0),(93,'2009-02-08 04:58:14','Some Useful Czech Phrases','<p>One of the very few advantages of Prague being absolutely crammed full of tourists is that you\'re more likely to hear english being spoken that czech. However the Czechs are always very impressed when you make any attempt whatsoever to speak their crazy language. I\'ve been in classes for three hours a week for eight months now and let me tell you, it\'s hard! Nevertheless, its worth learning a few phrases so you can at least raise a smile on the face of the the pleasantly-surprised waiter or waitress when you attempt to place your order in the local lingo. \\more</p>\r\n<p>So..... here are some of the most important phrases that you need.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" border=\"0\" style=\"width: 558px; height: 618px;\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>english</th>\r\n            <th>czech</th>\r\n            <th>pronounced</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>hello</b></td>\r\n            <td>dobry den</td>\r\n            <td><i>dob-ree den             </i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>goodbye</b></td>\r\n            <td>nashledanou</td>\r\n            <td><i>nas-cla-dannow</i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>a beer</b></td>\r\n            <td>pivo</td>\r\n            <td><i>pivow (note the short \'i\' as in \'list\'&gt;<br />\r\n            </i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>two beers</b></td>\r\n            <td>dve piva</td>\r\n            <td><i>dvyair pivver             </i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>please</b></td>\r\n            <td>pros&iacute;m</td>\r\n            <td><i>prosseem</i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>thankyou</b></td>\r\n            <td>diky</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <p><i>dee-key</i></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>white wine</b></td>\r\n            <td>bil&eacute; vino</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <p><i>bee-lair vee-no              </i></p>\r\n            <p><i>(the \'o\' at the end is short like the \'o\' in \'lost\')</i></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>red wine</b></td>\r\n            <td>cerven&eacute; vino</td>\r\n            <td><i>chair-ven-air vee-no</i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td><b>I\'ll have</b></td>\r\n            <td>d&aacute;m si</td>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <p><i>darm-si</i></p>\r\n            <p><i>(the &iuml;\' is short like the \'i\' in \'list\')</i></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;<b>and</b></td>\r\n            <td>a</td>\r\n            <td><i>pronounced short as in \'cat\'</i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;<b>cheers !</b></td>\r\n            <td>na zdravy !</td>\r\n            <td><i>na-zdra-vee ! (literally meaning &quot;to health !&quot; )</i></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For example, you walk into a pub, sit down at a table and say to the waitress....</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><b>&quot;Dobry den, dam si dve piva, cervene vino a bile vino prosim&quot;</b></p>\r\n<p>The waitress then goes off. When she comes back with your drinks you say...</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><b>&quot;Diky&quot;</b></p>\r\n<p>Then you raise a toast to everyone\'s good health and everyone chinks glasses making sure to make eye contact with the person who they are chinking with and saying as they do so....</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><b>&quot;na zdravy!&quot;</b></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>One last phrase you might want to learn.... <strong>hodne stesti!</strong> (pronounced <em>&quot;hod-nyay styest-yee&quot;</em>), meaning .....</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">.....GOOD LUCK !</p>',00001711,NULL,'right','some average czech words','yes','no',5,20,0,NULL,'yes',0),(95,'2009-02-08 04:57:08','Sightseeing around Prague','<p>Petra has drawn up a list of sightseeing tours that you might be interested in doing while you\'re over for the Wedding.</p>\r\n<p>\\more</p>\r\n<p>1.	The cheapest alternative, designed mainly for young people</p>\r\n<p><b>Free Prague Tours</b> <a href=\"http://www.freepraguetours.eu\">www.freepraguetours.eu</a></p>\r\n<p>7 days a week, rain or shine, no reservation necessary &ndash; meeting point on the Old Town Square on the corner of Parizska Street</p>\r\n<p>They offer:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>free tours daily at 10 30 a.m. and 2 p.m. &ndash; no official price for the tour, if you are happy you tip the guide (about CZK 200 would be just right)</li>\r\n    <li>magic flashlight tour every night at 8 p.m. &ndash; about the mysteries of Prague, price CZK 200, includes beer in a pub</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2.	Sightseeing tours in small groups, focused on walks in Prague and river trips, run by very nice people</p>\r\n<p><b>Walks of Prague</b> <a href=\"http://www.walksofprague.cz \">www.walksofprague.cz </a></p>\r\n<p>They offer two main tours that take in most of the Prague&rsquo;s beauty:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The superior tour of Prague &ndash; includes a boat trip, tram ride, lunch and a CD, lasts for 6 hours, meeting point at Orloj (the astrological clock) on the Old Town Square at 10 am daily</li>\r\n    <li>The Grand Tour of Prague &ndash; the same without the boat trip and lunch, lasts for 4 hours, starts daily at 11 am and 2 pm on the Old Town Square.</li>\r\n    <li>12 other shorter trips including boat cruises (also &lsquo;dinner on the river&rsquo;), tour of 1000 years of history, communism walk, the old Jewish quarter, tour of famous pus etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Alternatively if you don&rsquo;t want to walk with other strangers tourists you can email them and agree on an individual walk anywhere you like for a very reasonable price (discounts for groups).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3.	Sightseeing tours run by a large agency, focused not only on Prague but do also bus trips around the country.</p>\r\n<p><b>Prague Sightseeing Tours</b> <a href=\"http://www.pstours.cz\">www.pstours.cz</a></p>\r\n<p>Apart from Prague they offer bus trips to UNESCO sites, spa towns, castles and chateaus, folklore music etc.</p>\r\n<p>Their Prague tours start in front of the Municipal House at 9:30 am, you have to buy a ticket in advance (as it might be sold out) in a yellow stand opposite to the Municipal House. There they give you information about all of the other trips they do.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><i>NB We haven\'t taken any of these tours ourselves so we can\'t really recommend any of them but these are supposed to be good ones.</i></p>',00001713,NULL,'left','The Charles Bridge (you have to get up pretty early to see it this empty though)','yes','no',5,5,0,NULL,'yes',0),(96,'2009-02-08 04:56:56','Wedding DJ competition! --- UPDATED 30/4/08','<p>Roll up, Role up! all you wanna-be-wedding DJs...Now\'s your chance to prove to yourself and to everyone else that you\'re worthy of the title of &quot;Superstar Wedding DJ&quot;.\\more</p>\r\n<p>The band we booked have had to cancel so in their place we\'ll be holding this brilliantly conceived competition!</p>\r\n<p>....so, if you\'ve ever fancied yourself a budding wedding-jock then spare some time this week to choose your selection of dancefloor fillers and either bring them on CDs or save them on a memory stick or just load them onto your iPod. Failing that burn them all onto a CD in normal CD or MP3 format (make 2 copies) and make sure you bring them to the Reception. If you can\'t do any of those then send me your play list by email and I\'ll make sure your tracks are in an iTunes playlist with your name on it on the night. How easy is that?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Rules:</b></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Anyone can enter (as long as you\'re invited to the wedding)</li>\r\n    <li>Wedding DJs play in a randomly selected order</li>\r\n    <li>You get to play five tunes of your own choice</li>\r\n    <li>No dodgy music (if the dancefloor says &quot;booh&quot; - hit the skip button!)</li>\r\n    <li>The winner will be selected by the judges</li>\r\n    <li>The judges\' decision is final</li>\r\n    <li>Prizes will be awarded for the Superstar Wedding DJ and the two runners up</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>UPDATE</b></p>\r\n<p>Liz Pugh and Andrew Stratford have very kindly offered compere and stage manage the proceedings thus releasing Petra and I from that duty so that we may enjoy your superstar wedding DJ performances to the full. Thanks Liz and Strat.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001714,NULL,'right','Our favourite house cat','yes','no',5,4,0,NULL,'yes',0),(97,'2008-05-07 03:16:58','Getting to the ceremony on time','<p>Our original plan was to lay on a bus that would drive around Prague city centre picking you all up from your various hotels and apartments. As it happens it turns out that this is too much of a logistical problem so we\'ve abandoned the idea unfortunately for you.</p>\r\n<p>Your best bet to get to Vrtbovska Zahrada on time is to book a taxi to pick you up from wherever you are staying at around 10:30 so that you arrive at Vrtbovska by 11:00am.</p>\r\n<p>People staying within walking distance obviously won\'t need to bother with a taxi so make sure you take a good look at the map <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/images/user/city-detail.gif\">HERE</a> and if you decide to walk from the Old town over the Charles Bridge then allow yourselves at least half an hour - it might not look that far but tourists walk slowly and overtaking on the bridge is strictly prohibited by the sheer volume of them.</p>',00000001,NULL,'right','','no','yes',5,3,0,NULL,'yes',0),(98,'2009-02-08 04:57:14','How to get to the ceremony on time','<p>Our original plan was to lay on a bus that would drive around Prague city centre picking you all up from your various hotels and apartments. As it happens it turns out that this is too much of a logistical problem so we\'ve abandoned the idea unfortunately for you. Soz.\\more</p>\r\n<p>Your best bet to get to Vrtbovska Zahrada on time is to book a taxi to pick you up from wherever you are staying at around 10:30 so that you arrive at Vrtbovska by 11:00am.</p>\r\n<p>People staying within walking distance obviously won\'t need to bother with a taxi so make sure you take a good look at the map <a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/xoundboy4/images/user/city-detail.gif\">HERE</a> and if you decide to walk from the Old town over the Charles Bridge then allow yourselves at least half an hour - it might not look that far but tourists walk slowly and overtaking on the bridge is strictly prohibited by the sheer volume of them.</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re staying at Sir Toby\'s&nbsp; please don\'t rely on taking a tram - its not a quick journey You\'ll definitely need to grab a cab. It should only cost around 200Kc (six quid) so it shouldn\'t break the bank.</p>',00001715,NULL,'right','Be there by 11:00am','yes','no',5,6,0,NULL,'yes',0),(99,'2009-02-08 04:56:53','Recommended Places to Eat','<h2>Brazilian</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ambi.cz/index_eng.php\">Brasillero</a> - The best restaurant in the World (IMHO)</p>\r\n',00000001,NULL,'right','','yes','no',5,3,0,NULL,'yes',0),(100,'2008-04-28 18:17:58','Invitations','',00000001,NULL,'right','','no','no',12,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(211,'2008-04-28 18:33:36','Wedding Presents','href=\"https://www.johnlewisgiftlist.com/giftint/JSPs/GiftList/CustomerServices/CustomerService3.jsp\">HERE</a></li>',00001687,NULL,'right','Don\'t get us one of these please','yes','no',12,2,0,NULL,'yes',0),(212,'2008-04-29 02:33:57','The Morning After the Night Before',NULL,NULL,NULL,'right','','no','no',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'yes',0),(213,'2009-02-08 04:56:48','The Evening Do','<p>Starting at 6.30pm the Evening Do will be taking place at Petrinske Terasy, the same as the afternoon Reception so you won\'t have to move.There will be a buffet, dancefloor and hopefully lots of fun and excitement.</p>\r\n<p>We have put up a free bar for wine, and soft drinks. However the free booze is limited unfortunately - so once it\'s gone - it\'s gone and from that point onwards you will have to pay for your own drinks. The manager has just informed us that their credit card machine is not working at the moment and that there are no cash machines anywhere in the park.So please make sure you have enough cash on you. Drinks should only cost about half of what they would in the UK.</p>\r\n<p>The party will finish at 1am at which point you may want to carry on. There are a couple of nice bars in Mala Strana that stay open late. Just roll yourselves down the hill, head over to the left and you <i>should</i> go far wrong:</p>\r\n<p><b>St Nicholas Cafe</b> &amp; <b>JJ Murphy\'s</b> are net to each other. Directions <a href=\"http://www.mapy.cz/#x=133034152@y=135951901@z=15@mm=ZP@sa=s@st=s@ssq=tr%C5%BEi%C5%A1t%C4%9B%20%20murphy\'s@sss=1@ssp=133028976_135947528_133041264_135959392\">HERE</a></p>\r\n<p>Over the road is another bar called <b>U Maleho Glena </b>that\'s very nice too.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to go clubbing then I\'m afraid you\'re on your own there. We\'ve no idea about night clubs in Prague! Too old now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',00001716,NULL,'left','','yes','no',5,2,0,NULL,'yes',0),(214,'2008-06-25 06:00:00','Photos','<p>Dear Everybody</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for helping make our Big Day so special. Here are some photos to remind you of the day.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>The Wedding Day</b></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=194\">Set 1 </a>- The Official Wedding Photographers\' film camera</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=198\">Set 2 </a>- The Official Wedding Photographers\' digital camera</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=195\">Set 3</a> -Taken by Eva Bezpalcova</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=196\">Set 4 </a>-Taken by Katka Horkova</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=197\">Set 5</a> - Taken by Tomas Cajska</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryview.cfm?galleryID=203\">Set 6 </a>- Taken by Radovan Vrbsky **NEW**</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>Sunday 4th May</b></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=199\">With friends at the Brazilian Restaurant</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b>The Honeymoon </b></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=200\">Ben\'s Camera</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.xoundboy.com/cfm/galleryView.cfm?galleryID=201\">Petra\'s Camera</a></p>',00002827,NULL,'right','','yes','no',5,1,0,NULL,'yes',0),(215,'2014-01-05 00:30:20','Changing career is difficult when you don\'t know quite which direction to take!','',00000001,NULL,'right','','no','no