ob satisfaction!','yes','De La Bola Roja','','0'),(303,00002,'Come Try',3758288,44,'Manchester, UK','2005-06-24 00:00:00',00012,960,'This was the first song we did together in a single six hour session. He asked me to make a whole album on the strength of it. ','no','Come Try','','0'),(302,00002,'Chocolate',3331196,2,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2005-12-24 00:00:00',00006,232,'','yes','Chocolate','','0'),(301,00002,'Changed',4875360,43,'Gorse Hill Studios','2003-10-24 00:00:00',00001,462,'Featured on \"Showcase Vol 2\" promo CD from Gorse Hill Studios','yes','Changed','','0'),(300,00002,'By the Sea',5253392,37,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2006-04-24 00:00:00',00006,473,'','yes','By the Sea','','0'),(299,00002,'Broken hearted',3285318,42,'Gorse Hill Studios','2001-12-24 00:00:00',00006,462,'Featured on \"Showcase Vol 1\" promo CD from Gorse Hill Studios','yes','Broken hearted','','0'),(298,00002,'Blastaz',2338920,41,'Gorse Hill Studios','2002-12-24 00:00:00',00012,461,'Featured on \"Showcase Vol 2\" promo CD from Gorse Hill Studios','yes','Blastaz','','0'),(297,00002,'Big Hole',5091585,27,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2005-10-24 00:00:00',00006,463,'Taken from the 2005 Durutti Column Album \"Keep Breathing\"','yes','Big Hole','','0'),(296,00002,'Better Days',3288150,40,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2006-03-24 00:00:00',00006,107,'This song took over a year to write and record. We got there eventually.','yes','Better Days','','0'),(295,00002,'Belfast Town Hall',10230806,2,'Studio 7, Chorlton, Manchester','2000-12-24 00:00:00',00006,957,'Commissioned by Walk the Plank Pyrotechnics for a fireshow that was due to take place off the roof of Belfast Town Hall at the stroke of midnight on New Years Eve 2000. Unfortunately the show was cancelled due to bad weather.','no','Belfast Town Hall','','0'),(294,00003,'Beautiful lady',4059036,39,'The Iguana Bar, Chorlon, Manchester','2001-12-24 00:00:00',00015,466,'Recorded live in the Iguana Bar in Chorlton, Manchester by Neil Burton on his portastudio. Bass and edits done later in the studio.','yes','Beautiful lady','','0'),(292,00002,'Back in Chorlton',4186349,2,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2006-04-24 00:00:00',00006,481,'Written after the trekking trip to Morocco that I made in October 2005','yes','Back in Chorlton','','0'),(291,00002,'Baby Darlin\'',4969447,38,'Gorse Hill Studios','2003-12-25 00:00:00',00012,959,'','yes','Baby Darlin&#39;','','0'),(290,00002,'Awaiting You',5158935,37,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2006-12-24 00:00:00',00006,473,'','yes','Awaiting You','','0'),(289,00002,'Another Day',5472336,2,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2005-12-25 00:00:00',00006,378,'This is the original instrumental backing track that I gave to Helen Serridge for her to write to. She wrote a song called &quot;Why&quot;.','yes','Another Day','','0'),(288,00002,'Akhiyan',4052766,36,'Gorse Hill Studios','2000-12-10 00:00:00',00012,490,'Apparently this sold quite a few copies in the Asian Garage record shops.','yes','Akhiyan','','0'),(287,00002,'Ailing Wisdom',7153850,2,'Studio 8, Chorlton, Manchester','2005-02-25 00:00:00',00006,378,'I got very heavily influenced by ambient dub music back in about 1992 when I heard the Positva Ambient Collection CD. Some of the tracks on that CD, like Orbital, Aphex Twin and even an early Moby track were amazingly well crafted and took the listener on some other-worldly journey that is especially good to listen to after a big night partying.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;\r\n\r\nAt the time I never had the equipment or the know-how to make that kind of music and by the time I did then I was completely wrapped up with producing other kinds of music instead. I decided to have a go at making an ambient dub track to see whether I was capable of it and this is the result. It took around 4 hours to finish but I listen to it now and it sounds like a lot more time was put into it.','yes','Ailing Wisdom','','0'),(286,00010,'Agua',2547956,35,'Taganga, Colombia